feature.description: probable disease-associated variant found in pediatric undifferentiated soft tissue sarcoma samples; somatic mutation; also found in a subset of human papillomavirus-negative head and neck squamous cell carcinomas; results in global decrease of H3K36me2 and H3K36me3 levels and increased H3K27me3 levels.
Phosphoserine; alternate; by AURKB, AURKC and RPS6KA5.
in GLM; non-brain stem pediatric glioblastoma and diffuse intrinsic pontine glioma; somatic mutation; results in a global decrease of H3K27me3 levels; dbSNP:rs1057519904.
Phosphoserine; alternate; by AURKB, AURKC, RPS6KA3, RPS6KA4 and RPS6KA5.
